{
  "texts": [
    "Due to the inherently high cost of query processing in highdimensional space, exact query methods are hard to scale to billion-scale high-dimensional vector sets.",
    "To handle webscale vectors, approximate nearest neighbor (ANN) indexes have been intensively studied, falling into three major categories: locality-sensitive hashing (LSH)-based [2,18,48], proximity graph-based [52,53], and product quantization (PQ)-based [29,39,87] approaches.",
    "A recent experimental study [7] provided a detailed benchmark for ANN indexes.Q.",
    "Learned data indexing1-Dimensional Learned Index.",
    "A 1-D learned index intrinsically functions as an error-bounded CDF model, scaled by the data size N. In their seminal work [44], Kraska et al."
  ]
